article.description: — Darnell Rogers scored 14 points as Maryland-Baltimore County beat Stony Brook 60-48 on Monday.
article.headline: Rogers scores 14 to lift UMBC over Stony Brook 60-48
article.linkText: Rogers scores 14 to lift UMBC over Stony Brook 60-48
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- — Darnell Rogers scored 14 points as Maryland-Baltimore County beat Stony Brook 60-48 on Monday. L.J. Owens and Brandon Horvath each added 13 points for UMBC (13-4, 9-3 America East Conference). R.J. Eytle-Rock had 11 points and seven rebounds. Rogers shot 4 for 6 from beyond the arc. Mouhamadou Gueye had 16 points and 11 rebounds for the Seawolves (8-10, 6-6). The Retrievers improve to 2-0 against the Seawolves for the season. UMBC defeated Stony Brook 71-65 on Sunday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
